<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Poland/78a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Poland (<persName type="to">Flack</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 333</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-28">June 28,
                                    1932</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Secretary of State refers to previous correspondence regarding
                                the President’s Proposal of June 20, 1931, for postponement of
                                inter-governmental <pb facs="0754" n="634" xml:id="pg_634"/> debts
                                and transmits for the information of the American Chargé d’Affaires
                                copy of the “Agreement between the Republic of Poland and the United
                                States of America, June 10, 1932”.<note n="63" xml:id="d440fn63">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Annual Report of the Secretary of the
                                        Treasury</hi>, 1932, pp. 302–303.</note>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>